values:
in 6 hours, I go for my chest surgery.&nbsp; I'm sort of freaking out because I knew today would eventually come, but now it's here.&nbsp; I'll sleep for a few hours, not even realize it, and it'll be time to go to the hospital.&nbsp; I've never had any kind of major surgery before, but I feel like its something everyone's been through and I'm really lame for being so nervous.&nbsp; I dont know.&nbsp; 

aaaaaanyway.&nbsp; I'll be at chilton hospital probably until thursday.&nbsp; visitors are welcome!&nbsp; After thursday, I'll be home, but bed-ridden for about two weeks.&nbsp; at this point, visitors are STRONGLY encouraged =D

I expect to see ALL OF YOU.&nbsp; 
jk.
but it'd be nice.&nbsp; =)

I'm coming up on my last 2 days at Rowan University.&nbsp; And I couldn't possibly be happier about that.

lately, I've been thinking alot.&nbsp; about everything.&nbsp; how I miss everything.&nbsp; how I miss my old life.&nbsp; I can't help but think that my whole life was just consumed in lies..&nbsp; and now, the "real" is just pouring out of everyone and everything.&nbsp; I look back on every memory I have and I want to laugh because they're so wonderful, everyone was so wonderful.&nbsp; but then I want to cry, because they're gone.&nbsp; and I dont think anything I'll ever have in the future will be as great. but then I begin to wonder if they're real, or if I was just blinded by happiness..&nbsp; 

I really hope they were real.&nbsp; I hope everything was real.&nbsp; because I dont want to think something fake could make me so happy.
